  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Surgical repair of perineal lesions after delivery is frequently associated with pain and
      discomfort interfering with the normal activities of the puerperium. The aim of this study
      was to compare perineal skin repair after episiotomy with adhesive glue versus a subcuticular
      suture, regarding the incidence of pain and wound complications.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
